The South African National Taxi Council has announced taxi fares won't go up by more than R7. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The South African National Taxi Council (Santaco) in Gauteng has announced that fares for taxis will go up from 1 July 2020. Local trips will increase by R4 - R5 while metro to metro trips are set to increase by a maximum of R7. READ: Commuters hit with taxi fare increase Cross provincial border trips will increase by R50. The decision comes after an earlier decision to more than double prices caused outrage. After a meeting between government and Santaco, it was agreed prices would be revised.